Latvia Ready to Invest 57.6 Million Lati in AirBaltic, Leta Says

-- B y   A a r o n   E g l i t i s
-- 
2011-09-27T15:16:52Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-27/latvia-ready-to-invest-57-6-million-lati-in-airbaltic-leta-says.html
 The Latvian government is ready to
invest 57.6 million lati ($110.7 million) in airline AirBaltic
AS as long as a set of conditions are met,  Leta  reported today,
citing Prime Minister Valdis Dombrovskis.  An AirBaltic shareholders meeting on the capital increase
is planned for Sept. 29, the Riga-based newswire reported.
Changes in the management and supervisory council and the
shareholderâ€™s agreement will be on the agenda, Leta said.  The state owns 52.6 percent of the airline while Baltic
Aviation Systems has 47.2 percent.  To contact the reporters on this story:
